  monumentInformation:
    monumentInformation:
    - title: Who Built It
      details:
      - The Great Wall was initially built by the Qin Dynasty under Emperor Qin Shi
        Huang in the 3rd century BCE.
      - "It was expanded and reinforced by later dynasties, notably the Han Dynasty
        (206 BCE\u2013220 CE) and the Ming Dynasty (1368\u20131644 CE)."
    - title: Where It Is Located
      details:
      - The Great Wall stretches across northern China, covering approximately 21,196
        kilometers (13,171 miles).
      - It spans from Shanhaiguan in the east to Jiayuguan in the west, crossing
        mountains, deserts, and grasslands.
    - title: When It Was Built
      details:
      - Construction of the earliest sections began in the 7th century BCE during
        the Warring States period.
      - The most well-preserved sections, seen today, were built during the Ming
        Dynasty between the 14th and 17th centuries CE.
    - title: Who Is It Protected By
      details:
      - The Great Wall was designated a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 1987 for its
        historical significance.
      - It is protected and maintained by the National Cultural Heritage Administration
        of China and various preservation organizations.
    - title: Why It Was Built
      details:
      - The Great Wall was built primarily to protect China from invasions by nomadic
        tribes and military incursions from the north.
      - It also served as a means of border control, trade regulation, and communication
        along the Silk Road, symbolizing the strength and unity of ancient China.
